    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "When working in `:terminal` I often find myself entering normal mode with `<C-\\><C-N>`, navigating to some string and pressing `yp` to copy it to the terminal prompt. As an example imagine this terminal session:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ widgetctl get widgets\r\nwidget-foo-version-42-abfffde8312\r\nwidget-foo-version-43-321caaba44\r\n$ widgetctl describe widget-foo-version-42-abfffde8312\r\nThis widget is fine\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat I would like to do is to press some hotkey after `widgetctl describe` to initiate a completion popup like `i_<C-N>` does for text buffers.\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`:  v0.4.3\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently? no\r\n- Operating system/version: any\r\n- Terminal name/version: xterm\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm\r\n\r\n\r\n",
