            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There is also https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/8805 . \r\n\r\nInsert-mode completion is implemented in a way that makes a lot of assumptions expecting INSERT mode behavior, which is of course quite different than TERMINAL mode. I'm not sure it makes sense to do what's literally asked here, but perhaps Nvim could provide a convenient mini-plugin that simulates the main use-case. \r\n\r\n> What I would like to do is to press some hotkey after `widgetctl describe` to initiate a completion popup like `i_<C-N>` does for text buffers.\r\n\r\nVimscript already has `getcompletion()`. but getting the text preceding the terminal-mode cursor would require some scripting.\r\n\r\nAnyways, with those elements plus some sort of floating-window menu system, this can be reasonably achieved. I suppose it makes sense as a core feature. PR welcome....",
